flowRoot.flowPara: PlantScan Imaging Platform: For each scanning day
Load pot onto PlantScan conveyor and scan QRCode
If QRCode is not in database, add new entry for it
Cameras use the database references to save files to PlantScan temporary storage SSDs
At the end of scanning for a day, operator triggers copying to NAS
At 7pm each night, camera configurations and images are batched using the BagIt layout inside of a ZIP archive and sent to Cherax
Once files are on Cherax, image processing batches are queued up on Pearcey (or in near future NCI Nectar Cloud)
Image processing pipeline creates meshes, point clouds, GIFs, CSV and other debug files.
Results are batched using a BagIt layout inside of a ZIP archive and sent to Cherax in a different location to the original files
High Resolution Plant Phenomics Centre, Canberra
Hume Data Centre, Canberra and Clayton Data Centre, Melbourne
